## Active Decisions

### Pricing: Monthly Retainer Only
- **Date:** 2026-03-01
- **What:** All client engagements are monthly retainer. No project-based or hourly billing.
- **Why:** Predictable revenue, deeper client relationships, better capacity planning. Hourly billing punishes efficiency and creates misaligned incentives.
- **Forecloses:** One-off projects, hourly consulting, website-only builds.
- **Revisit:** After reaching $50K MRR — may add a project tier for enterprise.

### Service Packaging: 3-Tier Structure
- **Date:** 2026-03-05
- **What:** Every service offered in 3 tiers — Growth ($2K-3K), Scale ($3K-5K), Dominate ($5K-8K).
- **Why:** Anchoring effect, easy upsell path, clients self-select into budget range. Eliminates custom scoping for every deal.
- **Forecloses:** Custom pricing per client, single-tier offers, value-based pricing experiments.
- **Revisit:** After 20 clients signed — adjust tiers based on actual delivery costs.

### Channel Strategy: Meta + Google Only (for now)
- **Date:** 2026-03-10
- **What:** Only offer Meta Ads and Google Ads management. TikTok and YouTube as add-ons only.
- **Why:** Team expertise is deepest here. Spreading across 4 platforms dilutes quality. Better to be exceptional at 2 than mediocre at 4.
- **Forecloses:** Standalone TikTok management, LinkedIn Ads, programmatic display.
- **Revisit:** Q3 2026 — hire dedicated TikTok buyer, then expand.

### Tooling: Alfred as Agency Brain
- **Date:** 2026-03-15
- **What:** Alfred MCP server is the central operations layer. All project management, reporting, and team communication runs through Alfred.
- **Why:** One install gives the AI copilot agency-grade capabilities. Reduces context-switching between tools. Skills teach the AI how to think about agency work.
- **Forecloses:** Using Notion/ClickUp/Monday as project management. Manual reporting workflows.
- **Revisit:** Permanent — expand Alfred, don't replace it.

### Client Communication: Weekly Updates, No Exceptions
- **Date:** 2026-03-08
- **What:** Every active client receives a written status update every Friday by 3PM.
- **Why:** Proactive communication prevents "what's happening?" emails. Builds trust. Makes renewals easier. Alfred automates the data pull.
- **Forecloses:** Ad-hoc updates, "we'll update when there's news" approach, client portal as replacement for personal updates.
- **Revisit:** Never. This is a cultural decision.

